<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: OPERA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'St. Francis' Notes: Peter Sellars will direct and Jose Van Dam will star in 
the Los Angeles Philharmonic's performances of Olivier Messiaen's monumental 5 
1/2-hour opera, "St. Francis of Assisi" at the Salzburg Festival in 1992. The 
opera will be conducted by Esa-Pekka Salonen, who will officially begin his 
tenure as the Philharmonic's music director in the fall of 1992. 
</P>
<P>
Van Dam will re-create the title role he originated for the opera's Paris 
premiere in 1983 and the opera will be performed in Los Angeles after the 
Salzburg performance. The Philharmonic will also perform three concerts at the 
festival, two conducted by Salonen, and one by Pierre Boulez. The announcements 
were made at a Tuesday press conference in Los Angeles by Gerard Mortier, who 
will assume the directorship of the Salzburg Festival in 1992. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
