<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: FILLMORE; 
</P>
<P>
PILOT, PASSENGER NOT HURT IN PLANE CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A private plane en route to Santa Barbara lost power Tuesday afternoon and 
crashed into the Santa Clara river bottom about five miles east of Fillmore, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Pilot Robert Fenske, 23, and his passenger, Jerry Meglin, 42, both of Santa 
Barbara, were not injured in the 3:30 p.m. crash. 
</P>
<P>
The single-engine plane, a Cessna 152, lodged its front wheel in the sand and 
flipped over, said Ken Maffei, a captain with the Ventura County Fire 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
The Federal Aviation Administration will investigate the cause of the crash. 
KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
