<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: REYNOLDS TO RETIRE AS BURBANK FIRE CHIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Burbank Fire Chief Curtis V. Reynolds announced Tuesday that he will retire 
Dec. 30 after nearly 33 years with the department. 
</P>
<P>
During Reynolds' 15 years as chief, the department developed a 
hazardous-materials team and expanded its emergency medical services. He has 
recently been head of a campaign to build a new fire and police headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
"I can leave with no regret, but with lots of good memories and a sense of 
satisfaction," Reynolds said in a memo distributed to members of the City 
Council at their meeting Tuesday night. 
</P>
