<HEADLINE>
<P>
246 ENGLISH FANS ARE EXPELLED AFTER 2-HOUR FIGHT WITH ITALIANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In what a British spokeswoman called "the worst incident involving English 
fans" at the World Cup, 246 backers of England's soccer team were taken into 
custody and then expelled from Italy on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities sent them back to England on an airliner chartered by the Italian 
government. 
</P>
<P>
Twenty people were treated in hospitals for injuries sustained in the two-hour 
battle at Rimini, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The incident happened after Italian fans started celebrating Italy's 2-0 
victory over Uruguay in Rome on Monday night. English fans drinking in a bar 
"started throwing bottles at the Italians and car windows were smashed," 
British Embassy spokeswoman Kay Coombs said. 
</P>
<P>
FIFA, soccer's governing body, rejected a West German appeal to overturn the 
one-game suspension of Rudi Voeller for a red card he received in the 2-1 
victory over the Netherlands last Sunday. Voeller is barred from the World Cup 
quarterfinal game Sunday against Czechoslovakia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
