<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CYPRESS; 
</P>
<P>
TRASH RATE HIKED TO $9.45 PER MONTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNDA NATALI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to higher fees at county landfill sites, the City Council this week 
approved a $1.69 increase in monthly residential trash rates. The new rate of 
$9.45 takes effect July 1. 
</P>
<P>
"This is a major increase," said City Manager Darrell Essex, "but one 
unfortunately brought on by landfills.". 
</P>
<P>
Since January, 1989, landfill rates have been steadily on the rise. Gate fees 
have risen from $6.12 a ton in 1989 to the current level of $17.75 a ton. 
George Briggeman, who operates a disposal service for several cities including 
Cypress, says costs for new landfills as well as operating existing landfills 
have forced the increases. 
</P>
<P>
Next month's increase probably won't be the last. Briggeman told the City 
Council that county officials predict landfill rates may nearly double by 1995. 
</P>
<P>
To counter the rate increases, several recycling proposals are currently being 
studied, Essex said. Recycling would decrease the amount of trash going to the 
landfills and thus reduce the costs, he said.LYNDA NATALI 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
