<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC SYMPHONY OFFICIALLY ACCEPTS $45,000 NEA GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pacific Symphony, which had announced that it would accept a $45,000 grant from 
the National Endowment for the Arts, has received official notification of the 
award and will indeed accept it, Pacific Symphony executive director Louis G. 
Spisto said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Several U.S. arts groups have rejected NEA subsidies rather than sign what is 
being described as an anti-obscenity pledge. 
</P>
<P>
Spisto said his organization will continue to fight for an NEA that does not 
restrict the content of artworks. Pro-NEA letters to legislators and concert 
audiences will continue through the summer, he said.ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
