<P>
MAN SOUGHT IN MASSACRE PROBE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An arrest warrant was issued today for an army officer accused of destroying 
evidence in the November massacre of six Jesuit priests, their cook and her 
teen-age daughter. 
</P>
<P>
The warrant for Lt. Col. Carlos Camilo Hernandez was issued by Judge Ricardo 
Zamora, who is handling the politically charged investigation. 
</P>
<P>
The charges accuse Camilo Hernandez of destroying the mission logs of troops 
accused of the shooting. Camilo, now an executive officer of the elite Belloso 
Battalion in the capital, is the former assistant director of the military 
college where the troops were stationed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
