<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
PEDESTRIAN INJURED IN HIT-RUN IN ANAHEIM; POLICE SEEK IDENTITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Highway Patrol was trying to identify a pedestrian who remained 
in critical condition today after he was struck by a car when he attempted to 
cross the west Riverside Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
The man was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange after the accident, about 
10:40 p.m. Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
CHP Officer Angel Johnson said the man was seen walking in the center divider 
west of Raymond Avenue in Anaheim before he stepped into the fast lane. 
</P>
<P>
A 39-year-old Yorba Linda woman swerved but could not avoid striking the 
pedestrian, Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
Another vehicle then rear-ended the Yorba Linda motorist and sped off. Johnson 
said investigators were seeking information from the public on the hit-and-run 
driver. 
</P>
<P>
The pedestrian suffered a broken pelvis and head, chest and other internal 
injuries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
